The paper deals with the problem of ON/OFF scheduling of self-powered base stations in cellular networks, taking into account energy harvesting uncertainty and the goal of minimizing operational costs. This problem is relevant to several areas of computer science, including networked systems (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), control systems (cs.SY), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and game theory (cs.GT). However, given the focus on wireless networks and energy harvesting, cs.NI and cs.IT are the most likely categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.DS, and cs.GT.
